==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*basjon'' (apparently ‘grape’), of unknown ultimate origin.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[beri]] (Dutch [[bes]]), Old High German [[beri]] (German [[Beere]]), Old Norse [[ber]], Gothic -𐌱𐌰𐍃𐌹 (in [[𐍅𐌴𐌹𐌽𐌰𐌱𐌰𐍃𐌹]] ‘grape’).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈberɪje/}}

===Noun===
'''beriġe''' {{f}} (plural '''[[berigan]]''')
# [[berry]]

